# AlgoMaster Online Judge - System Architecture

## 1. System Overview

AlgoMaster is a multi-tenant online judge platform designed for educational institutions. It supports six programming languages (C, C++, Java, Python, Go, JavaScript), provides sandboxed code execution using cgroups/seccomp, and delivers isolated service across schools/campuses.

The system uses a distributed multi-service architecture communicating via REST API, Redis Streams, WebSocket, and HTTP:

```
+----------------+       REST + WebSocket        +------------------+       Redis Streams + HTTP        +------------------+
|                | <---------------------------> |                  | <-----------------------------> |                  |
|   Frontend     |     :5173 (dev) / :80 (prod)  |   API Service     |     POST /submissions/{id}/results|  Judge Worker    |
|   React 19     |                              |   Axum + Rust    |                              |   Standalone     |
|   TypeScript   |                              |   :3000          |                              |  (Linux sandbox) |
+----------------+                              +--------+---------+                              +------------------+
                                                         |                                            |
                                                         |  sqlx (PgPool)                              |  sqlx (PgPool)
                                                         v                                            v
                                               +------------------+                        +------------------+
                                               |   PostgreSQL 16  |                        |   PostgreSQL 16  |
                                               +------------------+                        +------------------+
                                                         |
                                                         |  deadpool-redis
                                                         v
                                               +------------------+
                                               |    Redis 7       |
                                               | (cache, queues,  |
                                               |  JWT blacklist)  |
                                               +------------------+

+------------------+       HTTP (feature flags)      +------------------+
|                  | <----------------------------> |                  |
|   API Service    |     :3000 (gateway client)     | Feature Gateway  |
|                  |                              |   Standalone     |
+------------------+                              +   :3001          |
                                                 +--------+---------+
                                                          |
                                                          |  sqlx (PgPool)
                                                          v
                                                +------------------+
                                                |   PostgreSQL 16  |
                                                +------------------+
```

**Core Architectural Features:**

- **Multi-tenant Data Isolation**: Query-level isolation ensures all domain queries filter by `organization_id`, preventing data leakage between tenants
- **Async Decoupled Judging**: Submissions flow to workers via Redis Streams, completely decoupling API from judging
- **In-process WebSocket**: WebSocket server runs co-located with API for millisecond real-time push
- **Workspace-level Shared Types**: Rust workspace shares core types (`Claims`, `Role`, `Permission`) via `shared` crate
- **Feature Gateway**: Standalone service for runtime feature flag resolution with scoped hierarchy

