## 3. Middleware Pipeline

Axum router stacks middleware in the following order (outer to inner):

```
Request
  |
  v
[1] CORS (tower_http::CorsLayer)
  |     Supports configured specific origins (prod) or wildcard * (dev)
  v
[2] Request ID (injects unique tracing ID)
  v
[3] Metrics (records request duration and status code)
  v
[4] Rate Limiting (tower_governor: 30 requests/minute/IP)
  |     Applied only to user-facing endpoints
  |     Excludes: health probes, metrics, worker heartbeat
  v
[5] Auth Middleware (JWT validation + Redis blacklist check)
  |     Injects: Claims, user_id (UUID)
  |     Supports sources: Authorization: Bearer header or access_token cookie
  v
[6] Tenant Middleware (extracts school_id from Claims)
  |     Injects: TenantContext { tenant_id }
  |     Never reads tenant info from client request headers
  v
[7] Feature Gate Middleware (optional, per-route)
  |     Checks feature flags via Feature Gateway
  |     Blocks disabled features with 403 Forbidden
  v
Route Handler
```

**Unrestricted Endpoints** (no rate limiting, no auth): `/health/live`, `/health/ready`, `/health`, `/status`, `/metrics`, `/internal/worker/heartbeat`

**Rate-limited Public Endpoints**: `/auth/login`, `/auth/register`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/logout`, `/ws`

**Rate-limited Protected Endpoints**: All `/users/*`, `/problems/*`, `/contests/*`, etc.

