## 4. Data Flows

### 4.1 Submission Lifecycle

Complete path from user code submission to real-time result display:

```
1. User submits code
   Frontend -> POST /submissions -> API Service

2. API validates and enqueues
   API -> XADD submissions {data: SubmissionMessage, school_id, submitted_at}
   API -> WebSocket broadcast SubmissionUpdate (status: "queued")

3. Worker dequeues and processes
   Worker -> XREADGROUP GROUP judge_workers {consumer} COUNT 1 STREAMS submissions >
   Worker -> Fetch test cases from PostgreSQL
   Worker -> Compile source code (if needed)
   Worker -> Execute in sandbox (cgroups + seccomp)
   Worker -> Compare actual output vs expected output

4. Worker sends results to API
   Worker -> POST /submissions/{id}/results {JudgeResult}
   Worker -> XACK submissions {message_id}

5. API stores results and notifies
   API -> UPDATE submissions SET status, score, ...
   API -> WebSocket broadcast SubmissionUpdate (status: "accepted"/"wrong_answer"/...)
```

**Priority Mechanism**: Worker reads from two streams — `submissions:contest` (high priority) and `submissions` (normal). "Parking" algorithm ensures contest submissions are always processed before normal submissions, even when normal messages are already read.

**Enqueue Metadata** (from `domain-submissions/src/queue.rs`):

```rust
// XADD fields include:
fields = vec![
    ("submission_id", submission_id.to_string()),
    ("data", message_json),                          // Serialized SubmissionMessage
    ("submitted_at", chrono::Utc::now().to_rfc3339()),  // Enqueue timestamp (wait time calc)
    ("source_stream", stream_name.to_string()),      // Source stream (DLQ retry routing)
    ("school_id", school_id.to_string()),            // Tenant isolation
];
// If contest_id exists, additionally include:
fields.push(("contest_id", cid.to_string()));
```

**Failure Handling Strategy:**

| Failure Type | Handling |
|-------------|----------|
| Processing errors (compilation failure, etc.) | Log error, ACK message (prevent infinite retry) |
| API callback failures | 3 retries with exponential backoff (2s, 4s, 8s + random jitter 0-499ms) |
| Retry exhaustion | Write to DLQ stream `submissions:dlq` with full metadata |
| Worker crash | Recover on next startup via XPENDING/XCLAIM |

### 4.2 Authentication Flow

```
1. Login
   POST /auth/login {username, password}
   API -> Verify password (bcrypt hash, supports MD5 transparent upgrade to bcrypt)
   API -> Generate access_token (JWT, 15min) + refresh_token (JWT, 7d)
   API -> Return {token, refresh_token, user}

2. Request Authentication (middleware chain)
   Request -> auth_middleware:
     Extract JWT from Authorization: Bearer header or access_token cookie
     Validate signature and expiration
     Check Redis blacklist: EXISTS bl:{jti}
     Inject Claims + user_id (UUID) into request extensions
   Request -> tenant_middleware:
     Extract school_id from Claims (never from client request headers)
     Inject TenantContext { tenant_id } into request extensions

3. Token Refresh
   POST /auth/refresh {refresh_token} or from refresh_token cookie
   API -> Validate refresh token
   API -> Generate new access_token
   API -> Return {token}

4. Logout
   POST /auth/logout
   API -> Write JWT ID to Redis blacklist: SET bl:{jti} EX 900
   Token rejected by auth_middleware until blacklist TTL expires
```

**JWT Claims Structure:**

```json
{
  "sub": "uuid",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "role": "teacher",
  "school_id": 42,
  "campus_id": 10,
  "iat": 1700000000,
  "exp": 1700000900,
  "jti": "uuid"
}
```

### 4.3 Contest Flow

```
1. Create Contest (teacher/admin)
   POST /contests -> Create contest record -> Set time window and problems

2. User Registration
   POST /contests/{id}/register -> Check time window -> Register as participant

3. Submit to Contest (via priority queue for preferred processing)
   POST /submissions (with contest_id)
   API -> XADD submissions:contest {data, contest_id, school_id, ...}
   Worker -> Prioritize consumption from submissions:contest stream

4. Live Rankings
   API -> WebSocket push LeaderboardUpdate to subscribers
   Frontend -> Real-time leaderboard table updates

5. Contest End
   API -> Generate leaderboard snapshot -> Save final rankings
```

