## 7. Circuit Breakers

Two in-memory circuit breakers protect workers from cascading failures:

| Breaker | Threshold | Half-open Timeout | Purpose |
|---------|-----------|-------------------|---------|
| Redis Breaker | 5 consecutive failures | 30 seconds | Prevent hanging when Redis unavailable |
| API Breaker | 5 consecutive failures | 30 seconds | Prevent hanging when API unavailable |

**State Machine:**

```
Closed (normal) → 5 consecutive failures → Open (reject requests)
Open (rejecting) → Wait 30s → HalfOpen (probe)
HalfOpen (probe) → Success → Closed (recovered)
HalfOpen (probe) → Failure → Open (reject again)
```

When API breaker is Open, judge results are written directly to DLQ instead of being dropped. Breaker state is in-memory (not persisted), resetting on worker restart—acceptable since restart itself is a recovery mechanism.

