| Root | 21 | All permissions |
| GradeAdmin | 12 | User/problem/contest/class/grade management + leaderboard/stats/tags |
| CampusAdmin | 10 | User/problem/contest/class/campus management + leaderboard/stats |
| Teacher | 11 | Problem/contest/class management + submit/grade + leaderboard/stats |
| TeachingAssistant | 6 | View problems/submissions/grade/class stats + leaderboard |
| Student | 3 | Submit code, register contests, view leaderboard |

`RbacService` uses in-memory `HashSet<Permission>` matrix mapping roles to permission sets. Route handlers use Axum middleware extractors:

- `require_permission(Permission)` — Single permission gate
- `require_any_permission(&[Permission])` — Any-match gate
- `require_all_permissions(&[Permission])` — All-match gate
- `require_min_role(Role)` — Hierarchical role check

### 8.3 Worker Authentication

Judge workers authenticate to API via shared secret (`WORKER_SECRET`) using `X-Worker-Secret` request header. This is completely independent from JWT-based user authentication, used only for:

- Result callbacks: `POST /submissions/{id}/results`
- Heartbeat reporting: `POST /internal/worker/heartbeat`

### 8.4 Password Security

- New user passwords hashed with `bcrypt`
- Legacy passwords from MySQL migration (MD5 hashed) support transparent upgrade: verify MD5 hash on login then auto-rehash to bcrypt
- Production environment requires `JWT_SECRET` and `WORKER_SECRET` to be explicitly set

### 8.5 Sandbox Security

Judge sandbox uses three-layer isolation:

| Layer | Technology | What It Limits |
|-------|-----------|----------------|
| Resource Limits | cgroups | CPU time (`cpu_time_limit_ms`), memory (`memory_limit_bytes`, default 256MB), process count (`pids_max`, default 64) |
| Filesystem | chroot | Isolated to `/var/lib/onlinejudge/sandbox`, limits file access scope |
| Syscall Filtering | seccomp | Filters dangerous syscalls, only allows minimal syscall set for judging |

`SandboxConfig` defaults:

```rust
SandboxConfig {
    sandbox_root: "/var/lib/onlinejudge/sandbox",
    cpu_time_limit_ms: 2000,
    memory_limit_bytes: 268_435_456,  // 256 MB
    pids_max: 64,
}
```

