## 9. WebSocket Architecture

WebSocket server runs co-located with API service. Clients connect via `/ws` endpoint and can subscribe to topics.

### 9.1 Message Types

Using `#[serde(tag = "type")]` tagged union pattern:

| Type | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `SubmissionUpdate` | Real-time judge progress (user's submissions) |
| `LeaderboardUpdate` | Leaderboard ranking changes |
| `Notification` | In-app notifications (specific user) |
| `ContestUpdate` | Contest status/time changes |
| `ProblemStats` | Problem submission statistics |
| `ChatMessage` | Contest discussion chat |
| `DiscussionReply` | Problem discussion new replies |
| `ArticleComment` | Blog article new comments |
| `TrendingArticles` | Blog trending articles update |
| `Ping` / `Pong` | Heartbeat keepalive |
| `Error` | Subscription or protocol errors |

### 9.2 Broadcast Scopes

| Method | Scope | Use Case |
|--------|-------|----------|
| `send_to_user(user_id)` | All WebSocket connections for a user | Personal notifications, submission progress |
| `send_to_topic(topic)` | All topic subscribers | `submission:{id}`, `contest:{id}` |
| `broadcast()` | All connected clients | System-wide announcements |
| `broadcast_to_tenant(school_id)` | All clients within tenant | Organization-level notifications |

### 9.3 Topic Access Control

| Topic Pattern | Access Control |
|---------------|----------------|
| `submission:{id}` | Submitter only |
| `contest:{id}` | Same organization users |
| `contest:{id}:chat` | Teachers + registered participants |
| `user:{uuid}` | Auto-subscribed (personal notifications) |
| `leaderboard:{scope}:{id}` | Public |

