## 12. Error Handling

### 12.1 API Error Handling

Unified `AppError` enum (defined in `api-infra/src/error.rs`) maps to HTTP status codes:

| Variant | HTTP Status | Use Case |
|---------|-------------|----------|
| `AppError::Auth(msg)` | 401 Unauthorized | JWT invalid or missing, token blacklisted |
| `AppError::Forbidden(msg)` | 403 Forbidden | Insufficient permissions or tenant mismatch |
| `AppError::NotFound(msg)` | 404 Not Found | Resource doesn't exist |
| `AppError::Validation(msg)` | 400 Bad Request | Invalid request body or parameters |
| `AppError::Database(msg)` | 500 Internal Server Error | Database query failed |
| `AppError::Internal(msg)` | 500 Internal Server Error | Unexpected server error |

Response body format:

```json
{
  "error": "Human-readable error description",
  "status": 401
}
```

Conversion chain: service methods return `anyhow::Result<T>`, route handlers auto-convert via `?` operator through `From<anyhow::Error> for AppError`.

### 12.2 Judge Worker Error Handling

| Error Category | Behavior |
|----------------|----------|
| Compilation failures | Return `JudgeResult { status: "compilation_error" }`, ACK message |
| Runtime errors | Return `JudgeResult { status: "runtime_error" }`, ACK message |
| Timeouts | Kill process, return `JudgeResult { status: "time_limit_exceeded" }`, ACK |
| Memory limits | Detected via cgroups, return corresponding status, ACK |
| Wrong answers | Return `JudgeResult { status: "wrong_answer" }` with per-case details, ACK |
| API callback failures | Retry 3 times (exponential backoff + jitter), then write to DLQ |
| Redis failures | Circuit breaker opens, skip consumption until recovered |
| Main loop errors | Exponential backoff: `min(1000ms * 2^error_count, 60s)` |

